[
  {
    "ID": 994902031,
    "key": "8c8cbe0b5b467c293e6ff037f61d6dc824b972071c51fb9d90ab3141649748bd",
    "original": "{Once an executioner in the many nomad tribes of the South, %name% was banished {for a beheading gone horribly wrong | when it was discovered he'd slain the wrong man | after he faked the death of a friend}. Aimless, he drifted into %randomcitystate% and resumed his trade in service of the viziers. | An executioner, %name% was tasked with beheading, hanging, quartering, and all the other punishments conveyed upon those criminals deemed unworthy of repaying their debts to the Gilder in life, and those who had been given the chance and failed. | %name% worked for %randomvizier% as an executioner, meting out grisly justice to the criminals of the South. | From his distinctive hood, it's clear %name% is an executioner. From his grim affect, it's clear he's been in the trade for some time.} {In the city states, however, even criminals are more valuable alive than dead, and soon he found himself running out of work and out of crowns. | One day he was charged with severing the neck of another headsman who had 'ruined' an execution by allowing the condemned to predict the killing blow and scream. %name% carried out his own task in silence, then decided it was time to find a new line of work. | For many years he was content with his work, but one day he was tasked with {hanging a young boy who had stolen food from the market | beheading a beautiful concubine who had displeased her master | drowning an old man too feeble even to stand}. He performed his duty, but found he no longer had a taste for the profession after that. | Though happy enough in his role, he learned that all of his predecessors had eventually been indebted or executed themselves after displeasing his employer. Seeing the writing on the wall, he began looking for a new line of work.} {Unsure what else to do, %name% decided mercenary work was a good fit for his skillset. | Figuring he'd be no less respected as a Crownling, but better paid, %name% now pursues a sellsword's career. | Accustomed to blood and blades alike, mercenary work is an obvious next step for %name%. | %name% tried his hand at a few occupations before deciding that his particular talents were best suited for the bloody, and well-paid, work of a sellsword.}",
    "translation": "{%name% 曾是南方众多游牧部落里的一名刽子手，因为 {一次惨不忍睹的斩首事故 | 被人发现他砍错了人头 | 伪造了友人的死亡来脱罪} 而被流放。漫无目的的他流浪到了%randomcitystate%，为了生计，他又重操旧业，成了维齐尔们的行刑人。 | 身为刽子手，%name%负责包括斩首、绞刑、车裂，以及所有其他刑罚 —— 施于那些不配活着向镀金者赎罪，或者错失了赎罪机会的人。 | %name% 曾为 %randomvizier% 效力，作为刽子手，向南方那些罪犯们降下血腥的正义。 | 从他那标志性的头罩可以看出，%name%是名刽子手。再加上他那阴郁的神情，他干这行已经有些年头了。} {然而在城邦，罪犯活着比死了更有价值，很快他便发现，自己活计越来越少，钱包也越来越瘪。 | 有一天，他受命去斩首另一名刽子手——那人因为让死刑犯预判到致命一击还发出尖叫，从而“搞砸”了一场处刑。%name%沉默着完成了自己的任务，然后决定是时候换个行当了。 | 多年以来，他对自己的工作都颇为满意，但有一天，他被派去{绞死一个在市场上偷了食物的少年 | 斩首一位惹怒主人的美丽侍妾 | 溺死一个虚弱到连站都站不稳的老人}。他履行了职责，但自那以后，他对这行再也提不起兴趣了 | 尽管对自己的角色还算满意，但他发现，所有前任刽子手最终都因为惹怒了雇主，要么贬为了负债者，要么被推上了断头台。眼看大事不妙，他开始寻找新的营生。} {不知道还能干什么，%name%觉得雇佣兵的工作挺适合自己这一身本事。 | 他寻思着，当个逐币者未必能比现在更不受人待见，赚的还肯定更多，%name%便踏上了佣兵之路。 | 习惯了血腥与刀剑，对%name%来说，佣兵活计是顺理成章的下一步。 | %name%试过几份不同的工作，最终认定，自己这身本事最适合干这种血腥但来钱快的卖命活。}%name%",
    "stage": 1,
    "context": "onBuildDescription = function onBuildDescription(){\n    return \"{Once an executioner in the many nomad tribes of the South, %name% was banished {for a beheading gone horribly wrong | when it was discovered he'd slain the wrong man | after he faked the death of a friend}. Aimless, he drifted into %randomcitystate% and resumed his trade in service of the viziers. | An executioner, %name% was tasked with beheading, hanging, quartering, and all the other punishments conveyed upon those criminals deemed unworthy of repaying their debts to the Gilder in life, and those who had been given the chance and failed. | %name% worked for %randomvizier% as an executioner, meting out grisly justice to the criminals of the South. | From his distinctive hood, it's clear %name% is an executioner. From his grim affect, it's clear he's been in the trade for some time.} {In the city states, however, even criminals are more valuable alive than dead, and soon he found himself running out of work and out of crowns. | One day he was charged with severing the neck of another headsman who had 'ruined' an execution by allowing the condemned to predict the killing blow and scream. %name% carried out his own task in silence, then decided it was time to find a new line of work. | For many years he was content with his work, but one day he was tasked with {hanging a young boy who had stolen food from the market | beheading a beautiful concubine who had displeased her master | drowning an old man too feeble even to stand}. He performed his duty, but found he no longer had a taste for the profession after that. | Though happy enough in his role, he learned that all of his predecessors had eventually been indebted or executed themselves after displeasing his employer. Seeing the writing on the wall, he began looking for a new line of work.} {Unsure what else to do, %name% decided mercenary work was a good fit for his skillset. | Figuring he'd be no less respected as a Crownling, but better paid, %name% now pursues a sellsword's career. | Accustomed to blood and blades alike, mercenary work is an obvious next step for %name%. | %name% tried his hand at a few occupations before deciding that his particular talents were best suited for the bloody, and well-paid, work of a sellsword.}\";;\n    return;\n}"
  }
]
